quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,43,"And among them are some who look at you, but can you guide the blind even though they have no sight"
  10,44,"Allah does not wrong people in the least, but it is people who wrong themselves"
  10,45,"On the Day when He will gather them, it will be as if they had not stayed [in this world] except for an hour of a day, they will recognize one another. Those who denied the meeting of Allah will be losers, for they did not follow guidance"
  10,46,"Whether We show you [O Prophet] some of that [punishment] of which We warn them, or We cause you to die, to Us is their return, and Allah is a Witness to all what they do"
  10,47,"For every people there is a messenger. When their messenger comes, it will be judged between them with justice, and they will not be wronged"
  10,48,"They say, “When will this warning come to pass, if you are truthful?”"
  10,49,"Say, “I have no power to harm or benefit myself, except by the Will of Allah.” For every people there is an appointed term; when their time comes, they can neither delay it for a moment, nor can they bring it forward"
  10,50,"Say, “What do you think, if His punishment were to overtake you by night or by day, what part of it would the wicked seek to hasten"
  10,51,Will you believe in it only after it befalls you? Now! While you used to seek its hastening?”
  10,52,"Then the wrongdoers will be told, “Taste the everlasting punishment! Are you being recompensed except for what you used to earn?”"
  10,53,"They ask you, “Is it true?” Say, “Yes, by my Lord. It is certainly true, and you cannot escape it.”"